\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
 We've been concentrating on formal letters in business communications, but today I'd like to talk about some issues in using e-mail. Actually, we'll be looking at this topic for the next couple of class sessions, as it's likely much of y
\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 our written communication in business will be done with e-mail - and the etiquette of using e-mail is extremely important in the business world.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 So, OK, there are two types of e-mails that you'll be using in business: internal, those sent within the off\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 ice, and the external - customers, suppliers, agencies.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Now, we discussed the paper letter and how it could get separated from its envelope. So it's essential for a paper letter to have all the receiver/sender information in the letter itself. Now, most\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
 e-mail programs include the receiver/sender information - so the message can't get separated from this information. But, there are a few options that some people are not aware of - and unfortunately, not all programs have all these options. OK. Let's say
\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
there are thirty people in the office where you work and you want to tell them about a change in policy. How do you set up your e-mail? I mean, who do you send this message to? What do you put into the box?
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Man Student:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  Well, I'd put the names into the \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
"to" box, you know, the box where I put the names of the people who will get the message.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  OK. So you would type all 30 names into the receiver box?
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Man Student:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  Well, probably not type. I might make a mistake. I'd copy them in - or u\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
se the "reply to all" icon from another e-mail, and of course, I change the message and the subject.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  OK. That is one way. Yes?
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Woman Student:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  Um, yeah, I have to do a lot of official e-mails, and I get really annoyed when people send
\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  me a message with lots of names in it. Sometimes I print out the message - and I get three pages of people's addresses for half a page of message.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  So what do you suggest?
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Woman Student:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  Well, I usually set up my address book so that\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
 I can put all the names of people into one group. And then when I want to send them all a message, I just put the name of the group into the receiver box - and then everyone gets the message. That way, if they print it out, then only the name of the grou
\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 p\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2  is on the page.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid7436902\charrsid7436902 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 Man Student:}{\insrsid7436902\charrsid1115228 \hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
 Yeah, I don't like that because . . . well, what annoys me is I need someone's address, right? So, I go to a message to get it and it isn't there - because just the group name is there. Or I want to see if everyone is on th\hich\af2\dbch\af12\loch\f2 
